  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Pathfinder #85: Fires of Creation pg. 60</em></p><h2 class=\"framing\">Statistics</h2><p><strong>Cost</strong> 2,400 gp</p><p><strong>Type</strong> light melee; <strong>Proficiency</strong> simple; <strong>Weight</strong> 2 lbs.</p><p><strong>Damage</strong> 1d6 (small), 1d6 (medium); <strong>Damage Type</strong> B; <strong>Critical</strong> x2</p><p><strong>Range</strong> -; <strong>Capacity</strong> 10; <strong>Usage</strong> see text; <strong>Special</strong> -</p><h2 class=\"framing\">Description</h2><p>While powered down, this sturdy, 2-foot truncheon functions as a light mace. Once it is activated (this is a swift action that consumes 1 charge), a high-density power core housed in the weapon's head generates a high-pitched whine that causes momentary disorientation in a creature struck. Each time the weapon hits a target, it consumes 1 charge and the creature struck must succeed at a DC 12 Fortitude save or suffer trauma to its central nervous system. For 1 round, a creature that fails its saving throw takes a �1 penalty on attack rolls, skill checks, and Will saving throws, as well as a �4 penalty on concentration checks. The duration of this effect stacks with multiple hits from the neural inhibitor. This is a mind-affecting effect.</p><h2 class=\"framing\">Construction</h2><p><strong>Craft</strong> DC 20; <strong>Cost</strong> 1,200 gp</p><p>Craft Technological Arms and Armor, military lab</p>",
